scene.message:
Maki: Is this town's{nl}
Sennen-Mannen Hall really{nl}
that strange?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: This market doesn't{nl}
seem to have a single decent{nl}
shop.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: So in this town you{nl}
can't get Sennen-Mannen{nl}
Hall's sweets, huh.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: This pot's nice~{nl}
{ctl08:2817}, hey, why don't you{nl}
gift this to me?{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Did you try talking to{nl}
the shopkeeper? Such a weird{nl}
face of makeup~!{waitkey}{ret}

Tsurunkamen: Ho ho ho ho...{nl}
Well come, indeed. What sort{nl}
of wares do you require?{waitkey}{ret}

Kamentsurun: Ho ho ho ho...{nl}
Gemstones I love above all{nl}
else.{waitkey}{clearbox}I'm running a blowout trade —{nl}
your gems for my treasured{nl}
wares.{waitkey}Care to give it a try?{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: If only I'd been{waitkey}a pretty boy like a puppy{nl}
caught in the rain, the Queen{nl}
might've taken to me~!{waitkey}{clearbox}Then I could've lived it easy{nl}
in the palace instead of a{nl}
dump like this~{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: The men in the{nl}
harem palace were submitting{nl}
to the Queen, weren't they.{waitkey}{clearbox}That's just pathetic, huh. Me,{nl}
I'm gonna live without{nl}
bowing to anyone.{waitkey}{ret}
